176bool ssl_client_cipher_list_contains_cipher(
177 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello, uint16_t id) {
178 CBS cipher_suites;
179 CBS_init(&cipher_suites, client_hello->cipher_suites,
180 client_hello->cipher_suites_len);
181
182 while (CBS_len(&cipher_suites) > 0) {
183 uint16_t got_id;
184 if (!CBS_get_u16(&cipher_suites, &got_id)) {
185 return false;
186 }
187
188 if (got_id == id) {
189 return true;
190 }
191 }
192
193 return false;
194}

196static bool negotiate_version(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
197 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
198 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
199 assert(!ssl->s3->have_version);
200 CBS supported_versions, versions;
201 if (ssl_client_hello_get_extension(client_hello, &supported_versions,
202 TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions)) {
203 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&supported_versions, &versions) ||
204 CBS_len(&supported_versions) != 0 ||
205 CBS_len(&versions) == 0) {
206 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
207 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
208 return false;
209 }
210 } else {
211 // Convert the ClientHello version to an equivalent supported_versions
212 // extension.
213 static const uint8_t kTLSVersions[] = {
214 0x03, 0x03, // TLS 1.2
215 0x03, 0x02, // TLS 1.1
216 0x03, 0x01, // TLS 1
217 };
218
219 static const uint8_t kDTLSVersions[] = {
220 0xfe, 0xfd, // DTLS 1.2
221 0xfe, 0xff, // DTLS 1.0
222 };
223
224 size_t versions_len = 0;
225 if (SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
226 if (client_hello->version <= DTLS1_2_VERSION) {
227 versions_len = 4;
228 } else if (client_hello->version <= DTLS1_VERSION) {
229 versions_len = 2;
230 }
231 CBS_init(&versions, kDTLSVersions + sizeof(kDTLSVersions) - versions_len,
232 versions_len);
233 } else {
234 if (client_hello->version >= TLS1_2_VERSION) {
235 versions_len = 6;
236 } else if (client_hello->version >= TLS1_1_VERSION) {
237 versions_len = 4;
238 } else if (client_hello->version >= TLS1_VERSION) {
239 versions_len = 2;
240 }
241 CBS_init(&versions, kTLSVersions + sizeof(kTLSVersions) - versions_len,
242 versions_len);
243 }
244 }
245
246 if (!ssl_negotiate_version(hs, out_alert, &ssl->version, &versions)) {
247 return false;
248 }
249
250 // At this point, the connection's version is known and |ssl->version| is
251 // fixed. Begin enforcing the record-layer version.
252 ssl->s3->have_version = true;
253 ssl->s3->aead_write_ctx->SetVersionIfNullCipher(ssl->version);
254
255 // Handle FALLBACK_SCSV.
256 if (ssl_client_cipher_list_contains_cipher(client_hello,
257 SSL3_CK_FALLBACK_SCSV & 0xffff) &&
258 ssl_protocol_version(ssl) < hs->max_version) {
259 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INAPPROPRIATE_FALLBACK);
260 *out_alert = SSL3_AD_INAPPROPRIATE_FALLBACK;
261 return false;
262 }
263
264 return true;
265}

267static UniquePtr<STACK_OF(SSL_CIPHER)> ssl_parse_client_cipher_list(
268 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
269 CBS cipher_suites;
270 CBS_init(&cipher_suites, client_hello->cipher_suites,
271 client_hello->cipher_suites_len);
272
273 UniquePtr<STACK_OF(SSL_CIPHER)> sk(sk_SSL_CIPHER_new_null());
274 if (!sk) {
275 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
276 return nullptr;
277 }
278
279 while (CBS_len(&cipher_suites) > 0) {
280 uint16_t cipher_suite;
281
282 if (!CBS_get_u16(&cipher_suites, &cipher_suite)) {
283 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ERROR_IN_RECEIVED_CIPHER_LIST);
284 return nullptr;
285 }
286
287 const SSL_CIPHER *c = SSL_get_cipher_by_value(cipher_suite);
288 if (c != NULL && !sk_SSL_CIPHER_push(sk.get(), c)) {
289 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
290 return nullptr;
291 }
292 }
293
294 return sk;
295}

297// ssl_get_compatible_server_ciphers determines the key exchange and
298// authentication cipher suite masks compatible with the server configuration
299// and current ClientHello parameters of |hs|. It sets |*out_mask_k| to the key
300// exchange mask and |*out_mask_a| to the authentication mask.
301static void ssl_get_compatible_server_ciphers(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
302 uint32_t *out_mask_k,
303 uint32_t *out_mask_a) {
304 uint32_t mask_k = 0;
305 uint32_t mask_a = 0;
306
307 if (ssl_has_certificate(hs)) {
308 mask_a |= ssl_cipher_auth_mask_for_key(hs->local_pubkey.get());
309 if (EVP_PKEY_id(hs->local_pubkey.get()) == EVP_PKEY_RSA) {
310 mask_k |= SSL_kRSA;
311 }
312 }
313
314 // Check for a shared group to consider ECDHE ciphers.
315 uint16_t unused;
316 if (tls1_get_shared_group(hs, &unused)) {
317 mask_k |= SSL_kECDHE;
318 }
319
320 // PSK requires a server callback.
321 if (hs->config->psk_server_callback != NULL) {
322 mask_k |= SSL_kPSK;
323 mask_a |= SSL_aPSK;
324 }
325
326 *out_mask_k = mask_k;
327 *out_mask_a = mask_a;
328}

330static const SSL_CIPHER *choose_cipher(
331 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello,
332 const SSLCipherPreferenceList *server_pref) {
333 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
334 const STACK_OF(SSL_CIPHER) *prio, *allow;
335 // in_group_flags will either be NULL, or will point to an array of bytes
336 // which indicate equal-preference groups in the |prio| stack. See the
337 // comment about |in_group_flags| in the |SSLCipherPreferenceList|
338 // struct.
339 const bool *in_group_flags;
340 // group_min contains the minimal index so far found in a group, or -1 if no
341 // such value exists yet.
342 int group_min = -1;
343
344 UniquePtr<STACK_OF(SSL_CIPHER)> client_pref =
345 ssl_parse_client_cipher_list(client_hello);
346 if (!client_pref) {
347 return nullptr;
348 }
349
350 if (ssl->options & SSL_OP_CIPHER_SERVER_PREFERENCE) {
351 prio = server_pref->ciphers.get();
352 in_group_flags = server_pref->in_group_flags;
353 allow = client_pref.get();
354 } else {
355 prio = client_pref.get();
356 in_group_flags = NULL;
357 allow = server_pref->ciphers.get();
358 }
359
360 uint32_t mask_k, mask_a;
361 ssl_get_compatible_server_ciphers(hs, &mask_k, &mask_a);
362
363 for (size_t i = 0; i < sk_SSL_CIPHER_num(prio); i++) {
364 const SSL_CIPHER *c = sk_SSL_CIPHER_value(prio, i);
365
366 size_t cipher_index;
367 if (// Check if the cipher is supported for the current version.
368 SSL_CIPHER_get_min_version(c) <= ssl_protocol_version(ssl) &&
369 ssl_protocol_version(ssl) <= SSL_CIPHER_get_max_version(c) &&
370 // Check the cipher is supported for the server configuration.
371 (c->algorithm_mkey & mask_k) &&
372 (c->algorithm_auth & mask_a) &&
373 // Check the cipher is in the |allow| list.
374 sk_SSL_CIPHER_find(allow, &cipher_index, c)) {
375 if (in_group_flags != NULL && in_group_flags[i]) {
376 // This element of |prio| is in a group. Update the minimum index found
377 // so far and continue looking.
378 if (group_min == -1 || (size_t)group_min > cipher_index) {
379 group_min = cipher_index;
380 }
381 } else {
382 if (group_min != -1 && (size_t)group_min < cipher_index) {
383 cipher_index = group_min;
384 }
385 return sk_SSL_CIPHER_value(allow, cipher_index);
386 }
387 }
388
389 if (in_group_flags != NULL && !in_group_flags[i] && group_min != -1) {
390 // We are about to leave a group, but we found a match in it, so that's
391 // our answer.
392 return sk_SSL_CIPHER_value(allow, group_min);
393 }
394 }
395
396 return nullptr;
397}

399static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_start_accept(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
400 ssl_do_info_callback(hs->ssl, SSL_CB_HANDSHAKE_START, 1);
401 hs->state = state12_read_client_hello;
402 return ssl_hs_ok;
403}

405// is_probably_jdk11_with_tls13 returns whether |client_hello| was probably sent
406// from a JDK 11 client with both TLS 1.3 and a prior version enabled.
407static bool is_probably_jdk11_with_tls13(const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
408 // JDK 11 ClientHellos contain a number of unusual properties which should
409 // limit false positives.
410
411 // JDK 11 does not support ChaCha20-Poly1305. This is unusual: many modern
412 // clients implement ChaCha20-Poly1305.
413 if (ssl_client_cipher_list_contains_cipher(
414 client_hello, TLS1_CK_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256 & 0xffff)) {
415 return false;
416 }
417
418 // JDK 11 always sends extensions in a particular order.
419 constexpr uint16_t kMaxFragmentLength = 0x0001;
420 constexpr uint16_t kStatusRequestV2 = 0x0011;
421 static CONSTEXPR_ARRAY struct {
422 uint16_t id;
423 bool required;
424 } kJavaExtensions[] = {
425 {TLSEXT_TYPE_server_name, false},
426 {kMaxFragmentLength, false},
427 {TLSEXT_TYPE_status_request, false},
428 {TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_groups, true},
429 {TLSEXT_TYPE_ec_point_formats, false},
430 {TLSEXT_TYPE_signature_algorithms, true},
431 // Java always sends signature_algorithms_cert.
432 {TLSEXT_TYPE_signature_algorithms_cert, true},
433 {TLSEXT_TYPE_application_layer_protocol_negotiation, false},
434 {kStatusRequestV2, false},
435 {TLSEXT_TYPE_extended_master_secret, false},
436 {TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions, true},
437 {TLSEXT_TYPE_cookie, false},
438 {TLSEXT_TYPE_psk_key_exchange_modes, true},
439 {TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share, true},
440 {TLSEXT_TYPE_renegotiate, false},
441 {TLSEXT_TYPE_pre_shared_key, false},
442 };
443 Span<const uint8_t> sigalgs, sigalgs_cert;
444 bool has_status_request = false, has_status_request_v2 = false;
445 CBS extensions, supported_groups;
446 CBS_init(&extensions, client_hello->extensions, client_hello->extensions_len);
447 for (const auto &java_extension : kJavaExtensions) {
448 CBS copy = extensions;
449 uint16_t id;
450 if (CBS_get_u16(&copy, &id) && id == java_extension.id) {
451 // The next extension is the one we expected.
452 extensions = copy;
453 CBS body;
454 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &body)) {
455 return false;
456 }
457 switch (id) {
458 case TLSEXT_TYPE_status_request:
459 has_status_request = true;
460 break;
461 case kStatusRequestV2:
462 has_status_request_v2 = true;
463 break;
464 case TLSEXT_TYPE_signature_algorithms:
465 sigalgs = body;
466 break;
467 case TLSEXT_TYPE_signature_algorithms_cert:
468 sigalgs_cert = body;
469 break;
470 case TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_groups:
471 supported_groups = body;
472 break;
473 }
474 } else if (java_extension.required) {
475 return false;
476 }
477 }
478 if (CBS_len(&extensions) != 0) {
479 return false;
480 }
481
482 // JDK 11 never advertises X25519. It is not offered by default, and
483 // -Djdk.tls.namedGroups=x25519 does not work. This is unusual: many modern
484 // clients implement X25519.
485 while (CBS_len(&supported_groups) > 0) {
486 uint16_t group;
487 if (!CBS_get_u16(&supported_groups, &group) ||
488 group == SSL_CURVE_X25519) {
489 return false;
490 }
491 }
492
493 if (// JDK 11 always sends the same contents in signature_algorithms and
494 // signature_algorithms_cert. This is unusual: signature_algorithms_cert,
495 // if omitted, is treated as if it were signature_algorithms.
496 sigalgs != sigalgs_cert ||
497 // When TLS 1.2 or below is enabled, JDK 11 sends status_request_v2 iff it
498 // sends status_request. This is unusual: status_request_v2 is not widely
499 // implemented.
500 has_status_request != has_status_request_v2) {
501 return false;
502 }
503
504 return true;
505}

507static bool extract_sni(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
508 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
509 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
510 CBS sni;
511 if (!ssl_client_hello_get_extension(client_hello, &sni,
512 TLSEXT_TYPE_server_name)) {
513 // No SNI extension to parse.
514 return true;
515 }
516
517 CBS server_name_list, host_name;
518 uint8_t name_type;
519 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&sni, &server_name_list) ||
520 !CBS_get_u8(&server_name_list, &name_type) ||
521 // Although the server_name extension was intended to be extensible to
522 // new name types and multiple names, OpenSSL 1.0.x had a bug which meant
523 // different name types will cause an error. Further, RFC 4366 originally
524 // defined syntax inextensibly. RFC 6066 corrected this mistake, but
525 // adding new name types is no longer feasible.
526 //
527 // Act as if the extensibility does not exist to simplify parsing.
528 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&server_name_list, &host_name) ||
529 CBS_len(&server_name_list) != 0 ||
530 CBS_len(&sni) != 0) {
531 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
532 return false;
533 }
534
535 if (name_type != TLSEXT_NAMETYPE_host_name ||
536 CBS_len(&host_name) == 0 ||
537 CBS_len(&host_name) > TLSEXT_MAXLEN_host_name ||
538 CBS_contains_zero_byte(&host_name)) {
539 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNRECOGNIZED_NAME;
540 return false;
541 }
542
543 // Copy the hostname as a string.
544 char *raw = nullptr;
545 if (!CBS_strdup(&host_name, &raw)) {
546 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
547 return false;
548 }
549 ssl->s3->hostname.reset(raw);
550
551 hs->should_ack_sni = true;
552 return true;
553}

555static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
556 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
557
558 SSLMessage msg;
559 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
560 return ssl_hs_read_message;
561 }
562
563 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CLIENT_HELLO)) {
564 return ssl_hs_error;
565 }
566
567 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
568 if (!ssl_client_hello_init(ssl, &client_hello, msg.body)) {
569 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
570 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
571 return ssl_hs_error;
572 }
573
574 // ClientHello should be the end of the flight. We check this early to cover
575 // all protocol versions.
576 if (ssl->method->has_unprocessed_handshake_data(ssl)) {
577 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNEXPECTED_MESSAGE);
578 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_EXCESS_HANDSHAKE_DATA);
579 return ssl_hs_error;
580 }
581
582 if (hs->config->handoff) {
583 return ssl_hs_handoff;
584 }
585
586 // If the ClientHello contains an encrypted_client_hello extension (and no
587 // ech_is_inner extension), act as a client-facing server and attempt to
588 // decrypt the ClientHelloInner.
589 CBS ech_body;
590 if (ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello, &ech_body,
591 TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello)) {
592 CBS unused;
593 if (ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello, &unused,
594 TLSEXT_TYPE_ech_is_inner)) {
595 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
596 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
597 return ssl_hs_error;
598 }
599
600 // Parse a ClientECH out of the extension body.
601 uint8_t config_id;
602 uint16_t kdf_id, aead_id;
603 CBS enc, payload;
604 if (!CBS_get_u16(&ech_body, &kdf_id) || //
605 !CBS_get_u16(&ech_body, &aead_id) ||
606 !CBS_get_u8(&ech_body, &config_id) ||
607 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_body, &enc) ||
608 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_body, &payload) ||
609 CBS_len(&ech_body) != 0) {
610 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
611 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
612 return ssl_hs_error;
613 }
614
615 {
616 MutexReadLock lock(&ssl->ctx->lock);
617 hs->ech_server_config_list = UpRef(ssl->ctx->ech_server_config_list);
618 }
619
620 if (hs->ech_server_config_list) {
621 for (const auto &ech_config : hs->ech_server_config_list->configs) {
622 hs->ech_hpke_ctx.Reset();
623 if (config_id != ech_config->config_id() ||
624 !ech_config->SetupContext(hs->ech_hpke_ctx.get(), kdf_id, aead_id,
625 enc)) {
626 // Ignore the error and try another ECHConfig.
627 ERR_clear_error();
628 continue;
629 }
630 Array<uint8_t> encoded_client_hello_inner;
631 bool is_decrypt_error;
632 if (!ssl_client_hello_decrypt(hs->ech_hpke_ctx.get(),
633 &encoded_client_hello_inner,
634 &is_decrypt_error, &client_hello, kdf_id,
635 aead_id, config_id, enc, payload)) {
636 if (is_decrypt_error) {
637 // Ignore the error and try another ECHConfig.
638 ERR_clear_error();
639 continue;
640 }
641 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECRYPTION_FAILED);
642 return ssl_hs_error;
643 }
644
645 // Recover the ClientHelloInner from the EncodedClientHelloInner.
646 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
647 bssl::Array<uint8_t> client_hello_inner;
648 if (!ssl_decode_client_hello_inner(ssl, &alert, &client_hello_inner,
649 encoded_client_hello_inner,
650 &client_hello)) {
651 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
652 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
653 return ssl_hs_error;
654 }
655 hs->ech_client_hello_buf = std::move(client_hello_inner);
656
657 // Load the ClientHelloInner into |client_hello|.
658 if (!hs->GetClientHello(&msg, &client_hello)) {
659 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
660 return ssl_hs_error;
661 }
662
663 hs->ech_config_id = config_id;
664 hs->ech_accept = true;
665 break;
666 }
667 }
668
669 // If we did not set |hs->ech_accept| to true, we will send the current
670 // ECHConfigs as retry_configs in the ServerHello's encrypted extensions.
671 // Proceed with the ClientHelloOuter.
672 }
673
674 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
675 if (!extract_sni(hs, &alert, &client_hello)) {
676 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
677 return ssl_hs_error;
678 }
679
680 hs->state = state12_read_client_hello_after_ech;
681 return ssl_hs_ok;
682}
683
684static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_hello_after_ech(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
685 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
686
687 SSLMessage msg_unused;
688 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
689 if (!hs->GetClientHello(&msg_unused, &client_hello)) {
690 return ssl_hs_error;
691 }
692
693 // Run the early callback.
694 if (ssl->ctx->select_certificate_cb != NULL) {
695 switch (ssl->ctx->select_certificate_cb(&client_hello)) {
696 case ssl_select_cert_retry:
697 return ssl_hs_certificate_selection_pending;
698
699 case ssl_select_cert_error:
700 // Connection rejected.
701 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CONNECTION_REJECTED);
702 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
703 return ssl_hs_error;
704
705 default:
706 /* fallthrough */;
707 }
708 }
709
710 // Freeze the version range after the early callback.
711 if (!ssl_get_version_range(hs, &hs->min_version, &hs->max_version)) {
712 return ssl_hs_error;
713 }
714
715 if (hs->config->jdk11_workaround &&
716 is_probably_jdk11_with_tls13(&client_hello)) {
717 hs->apply_jdk11_workaround = true;
718 }
719
720 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
721 if (!negotiate_version(hs, &alert, &client_hello)) {
722 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
723 return ssl_hs_error;
724 }
725
726 hs->client_version = client_hello.version;
727 if (client_hello.random_len != SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) {
728 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
729 return ssl_hs_error;
730 }
731 OPENSSL_memcpy(ssl->s3->client_random, client_hello.random,
732 client_hello.random_len);
733
734 // Only null compression is supported. TLS 1.3 further requires the peer
735 // advertise no other compression.
736 if (OPENSSL_memchr(client_hello.compression_methods, 0,
737 client_hello.compression_methods_len) == NULL ||
738 (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION &&
739 client_hello.compression_methods_len != 1)) {
740 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_COMPRESSION_LIST);
741 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
742 return ssl_hs_error;
743 }
744
745 // TLS extensions.
746 if (!ssl_parse_clienthello_tlsext(hs, &client_hello)) {
747 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PARSE_TLSEXT);
748 return ssl_hs_error;
749 }
750
751 if (hs->ech_present && hs->ech_is_inner_present) {
752 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
753 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
754 return ssl_hs_error;
755 }
756
757 hs->state = state12_select_certificate;
758 return ssl_hs_ok;
759}

761static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_select_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
762 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
763
764 // Call |cert_cb| to update server certificates if required.
765 if (hs->config->cert->cert_cb != NULL) {
766 int rv = hs->config->cert->cert_cb(ssl, hs->config->cert->cert_cb_arg);
767 if (rv == 0) {
768 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CERT_CB_ERROR);
769 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
770 return ssl_hs_error;
771 }
772 if (rv < 0) {
773 return ssl_hs_x509_lookup;
774 }
775 }
776
777 if (!ssl_on_certificate_selected(hs)) {
778 return ssl_hs_error;
779 }
780
781 if (hs->ocsp_stapling_requested &&
782 ssl->ctx->legacy_ocsp_callback != nullptr) {
783 switch (ssl->ctx->legacy_ocsp_callback(
784 ssl, ssl->ctx->legacy_ocsp_callback_arg)) {
785 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_OK:
786 break;
787 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_NOACK:
788 hs->ocsp_stapling_requested = false;
789 break;
790 default:
791 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_OCSP_CB_ERROR);
792 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
793 return ssl_hs_error;
794 }
795 }
796
797 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
798 // Jump to the TLS 1.3 state machine.
799 hs->state = state12_tls13;
800 return ssl_hs_ok;
801 }
802
803 // It should not be possible to negotiate TLS 1.2 with ECH. The
804 // ClientHelloInner decoding function rejects ClientHellos which offer TLS 1.2
805 // or below.
806 assert(!hs->ech_accept);
807
808 // TODO(davidben): Also compute hints for TLS 1.2. When doing so, update the
809 // check in bssl_shim.cc to test this.
810 if (hs->hints_requested) {
811 return ssl_hs_hints_ready;
812 }
813
814 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_protocol_version;
815
816 SSLMessage msg_unused;
817 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
818 if (!hs->GetClientHello(&msg_unused, &client_hello)) {
819 return ssl_hs_error;
820 }
821
822 // Negotiate the cipher suite. This must be done after |cert_cb| so the
823 // certificate is finalized.
824 SSLCipherPreferenceList *prefs = hs->config->cipher_list
825 ? hs->config->cipher_list.get()
826 : ssl->ctx->cipher_list.get();
827 hs->new_cipher = choose_cipher(hs, &client_hello, prefs);
828 if (hs->new_cipher == NULL) {
829 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_SHARED_CIPHER);
830 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
831 return ssl_hs_error;
832 }
833
834 hs->state = state12_select_parameters;
835 return ssl_hs_ok;
836}

838static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_tls13(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
839 enum ssl_hs_wait_t wait = tls13_server_handshake(hs);
840 if (wait == ssl_hs_ok) {
841 hs->state = state12_finish_server_handshake;
842 return ssl_hs_ok;
843 }
844
845 return wait;
846}

848static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_select_parameters(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
849 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
850
851 SSLMessage msg;
852 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
853 return ssl_hs_read_message;
854 }
855
856 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
857 if (!ssl_client_hello_init(ssl, &client_hello, msg.body)) {
858 return ssl_hs_error;
859 }
860
861 // Determine whether we are doing session resumption.
862 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session;
863 bool tickets_supported = false, renew_ticket = false;
864 enum ssl_hs_wait_t wait = ssl_get_prev_session(
865 hs, &session, &tickets_supported, &renew_ticket, &client_hello);
866 if (wait != ssl_hs_ok) {
867 return wait;
868 }
869
870 if (session) {
871 if (session->extended_master_secret && !hs->extended_master_secret) {
872 // A ClientHello without EMS that attempts to resume a session with EMS
873 // is fatal to the connection.
874 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RESUMED_EMS_SESSION_WITHOUT_EMS_EXTENSION);
875 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
876 return ssl_hs_error;
877 }
878
879 if (!ssl_session_is_resumable(hs, session.get()) ||
880 // If the client offers the EMS extension, but the previous session
881 // didn't use it, then negotiate a new session.
882 hs->extended_master_secret != session->extended_master_secret) {
883 session.reset();
884 }
885 }
886
887 if (session) {
888 // Use the old session.
889 hs->ticket_expected = renew_ticket;
890 ssl->session = std::move(session);
891 ssl->s3->session_reused = true;
892 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
893 } else {
894 hs->ticket_expected = tickets_supported;
895 ssl_set_session(ssl, nullptr);
896 if (!ssl_get_new_session(hs)) {
897 return ssl_hs_error;
898 }
899
900 // Assign a session ID if not using session tickets.
901 if (!hs->ticket_expected &&
902 (ssl->ctx->session_cache_mode & SSL_SESS_CACHE_SERVER)) {
903 hs->new_session->session_id_length = SSL3_SSL_SESSION_ID_LENGTH;
904 RAND_bytes(hs->new_session->session_id,
905 hs->new_session->session_id_length);
906 }
907 }
908
909 if (ssl->ctx->dos_protection_cb != NULL &&
910 ssl->ctx->dos_protection_cb(&client_hello) == 0) {
911 // Connection rejected for DOS reasons.
912 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CONNECTION_REJECTED);
913 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
914 return ssl_hs_error;
915 }
916
917 if (ssl->session == NULL) {
918 hs->new_session->cipher = hs->new_cipher;
919
920 // Determine whether to request a client certificate.
921 hs->cert_request = !!(hs->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_PEER);
922 // Only request a certificate if Channel ID isn't negotiated.
923 if ((hs->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_PEER_IF_NO_OBC) &&
924 ssl->s3->channel_id_valid) {
925 hs->cert_request = false;
926 }
927 // CertificateRequest may only be sent in certificate-based ciphers.
928 if (!ssl_cipher_uses_certificate_auth(hs->new_cipher)) {
929 hs->cert_request = false;
930 }
931
932 if (!hs->cert_request) {
933 // OpenSSL returns X509_V_OK when no certificates are requested. This is
934 // classed by them as a bug, but it's assumed by at least NGINX.
935 hs->new_session->verify_result = X509_V_OK;
936 }
937 }
938
939 // HTTP/2 negotiation depends on the cipher suite, so ALPN negotiation was
940 // deferred. Complete it now.
941 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
942 if (!ssl_negotiate_alpn(hs, &alert, &client_hello)) {
943 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
944 return ssl_hs_error;
945 }
946
947 // Now that all parameters are known, initialize the handshake hash and hash
948 // the ClientHello.
949 if (!hs->transcript.InitHash(ssl_protocol_version(ssl), hs->new_cipher) ||
950 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
951 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
952 return ssl_hs_error;
953 }
954
955 // Handback includes the whole handshake transcript, so we cannot free the
956 // transcript buffer in the handback case.
957 if (!hs->cert_request && !hs->handback) {
958 hs->transcript.FreeBuffer();
959 }
960
961 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
962
963 hs->state = state12_send_server_hello;
964 return ssl_hs_ok;
965}

967static void copy_suffix(Span<uint8_t> out, Span<const uint8_t> in) {
968 out = out.subspan(out.size() - in.size());
969 assert(out.size() == in.size());
970 OPENSSL_memcpy(out.data(), in.data(), in.size());
971}

973static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
974 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
975
976 // We only accept ChannelIDs on connections with ECDHE in order to avoid a
977 // known attack while we fix ChannelID itself.
978 if (ssl->s3->channel_id_valid &&
979 (hs->new_cipher->algorithm_mkey & SSL_kECDHE) == 0) {
980 ssl->s3->channel_id_valid = false;
981 }
982
983 // If this is a resumption and the original handshake didn't support
984 // ChannelID then we didn't record the original handshake hashes in the
985 // session and so cannot resume with ChannelIDs.
986 if (ssl->session != NULL &&
987 ssl->session->original_handshake_hash_len == 0) {
988 ssl->s3->channel_id_valid = false;
989 }
990
991 struct OPENSSL_timeval now;
992 ssl_get_current_time(ssl, &now);
993 ssl->s3->server_random[0] = now.tv_sec >> 24;
994 ssl->s3->server_random[1] = now.tv_sec >> 16;
995 ssl->s3->server_random[2] = now.tv_sec >> 8;
996 ssl->s3->server_random[3] = now.tv_sec;
997 if (!RAND_bytes(ssl->s3->server_random + 4, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE - 4)) {
998 return ssl_hs_error;
999 }
1000
1001 // Implement the TLS 1.3 anti-downgrade feature.
1002 if (ssl_supports_version(hs, TLS1_3_VERSION)) {
1003 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) == TLS1_2_VERSION) {
1004 if (hs->apply_jdk11_workaround) {
1005 // JDK 11 implements the TLS 1.3 downgrade signal, so we cannot send it
1006 // here. However, the signal is only effective if all TLS 1.2
1007 // ServerHellos produced by the server are marked. Thus we send a
1008 // different non-standard signal for the time being, until JDK 11.0.2 is
1009 // released and clients have updated.
1010 copy_suffix(ssl->s3->server_random, kJDK11DowngradeRandom);
1011 } else {
1012 copy_suffix(ssl->s3->server_random, kTLS13DowngradeRandom);
1013 }
1014 } else {
1015 copy_suffix(ssl->s3->server_random, kTLS12DowngradeRandom);
1016 }
1017 }
1018
1019 const SSL_SESSION *session = hs->new_session.get();
1020 if (ssl->session != nullptr) {
1021 session = ssl->session.get();
1022 }
1023
1024 ScopedCBB cbb;
1025 CBB body, session_id;
1026 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body, SSL3_MT_SERVER_HELLO) ||
1027 !CBB_add_u16(&body, ssl->version) ||
1028 !CBB_add_bytes(&body, ssl->s3->server_random, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) ||
1029 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &session_id) ||
1030 !CBB_add_bytes(&session_id, session->session_id,
1031 session->session_id_length) ||
1032 !CBB_add_u16(&body, SSL_CIPHER_get_protocol_id(hs->new_cipher)) ||
1033 !CBB_add_u8(&body, 0 /* no compression */) ||
1034 !ssl_add_serverhello_tlsext(hs, &body) ||
1035 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
1036 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1037 return ssl_hs_error;
1038 }
1039
1040 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
1041 hs->state = state12_send_server_finished;
1042 } else {
1043 hs->state = state12_send_server_certificate;
1044 }
1045 return ssl_hs_ok;
1046}

1048static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1049 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1050 ScopedCBB cbb;
1051
1052 if (ssl_cipher_uses_certificate_auth(hs->new_cipher)) {
1053 if (!ssl_has_certificate(hs)) {
1054 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_CERTIFICATE_SET);
1055 return ssl_hs_error;
1056 }
1057
1058 if (!ssl_output_cert_chain(hs)) {
1059 return ssl_hs_error;
1060 }
1061
1062 if (hs->certificate_status_expected) {
1063 CBB body, ocsp_response;
1064 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
1065 SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_STATUS) ||
1066 !CBB_add_u8(&body, TLSEXT_STATUSTYPE_ocsp) ||
1067 !CBB_add_u24_length_prefixed(&body, &ocsp_response) ||
1068 !CBB_add_bytes(
1069 &ocsp_response,
1070 CRYPTO_BUFFER_data(hs->config->cert->ocsp_response.get()),
1071 CRYPTO_BUFFER_len(hs->config->cert->ocsp_response.get())) ||
1072 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
1073 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1074 return ssl_hs_error;
1075 }
1076 }
1077 }
1078
1079 // Assemble ServerKeyExchange parameters if needed.
1080 uint32_t alg_k = hs->new_cipher->algorithm_mkey;
1081 uint32_t alg_a = hs->new_cipher->algorithm_auth;
1082 if (ssl_cipher_requires_server_key_exchange(hs->new_cipher) ||
1083 ((alg_a & SSL_aPSK) && hs->config->psk_identity_hint)) {
1084 // Pre-allocate enough room to comfortably fit an ECDHE public key. Prepend
1085 // the client and server randoms for the signing transcript.
1086 CBB child;
1087 if (!CBB_init(cbb.get(), SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE * 2 + 128) ||
1088 !CBB_add_bytes(cbb.get(), ssl->s3->client_random, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) ||
1089 !CBB_add_bytes(cbb.get(), ssl->s3->server_random, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE)) {
1090 return ssl_hs_error;
1091 }
1092
1093 // PSK ciphers begin with an identity hint.
1094 if (alg_a & SSL_aPSK) {
1095 size_t len = hs->config->psk_identity_hint == nullptr
1096 ? 0
1097 : strlen(hs->config->psk_identity_hint.get());
1098 if (!CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(cbb.get(), &child) ||
1099 !CBB_add_bytes(&child,
1100 (const uint8_t *)hs->config->psk_identity_hint.get(),
1101 len)) {
1102 return ssl_hs_error;
1103 }
1104 }
1105
1106 if (alg_k & SSL_kECDHE) {
1107 // Determine the group to use.
1108 uint16_t group_id;
1109 if (!tls1_get_shared_group(hs, &group_id)) {
1110 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1111 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
1112 return ssl_hs_error;
1113 }
1114 hs->new_session->group_id = group_id;
1115
1116 // Set up ECDH, generate a key, and emit the public half.
1117 hs->key_shares[0] = SSLKeyShare::Create(group_id);
1118 if (!hs->key_shares[0] ||
1119 !CBB_add_u8(cbb.get(), NAMED_CURVE_TYPE) ||
1120 !CBB_add_u16(cbb.get(), group_id) ||
1121 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(cbb.get(), &child) ||
1122 !hs->key_shares[0]->Offer(&child)) {
1123 return ssl_hs_error;
1124 }
1125 } else {
1126 assert(alg_k & SSL_kPSK);
1127 }
1128
1129 if (!CBBFinishArray(cbb.get(), &hs->server_params)) {
1130 return ssl_hs_error;
1131 }
1132 }
1133
1134 hs->state = state12_send_server_key_exchange;
1135 return ssl_hs_ok;
1136}
1137
1138static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_key_exchange(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1139 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1140
1141 if (hs->server_params.size() == 0) {
1142 hs->state = state12_send_server_hello_done;
1143 return ssl_hs_ok;
1144 }
1145
1146 ScopedCBB cbb;
1147 CBB body, child;
1148 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
1149 SSL3_MT_SERVER_KEY_EXCHANGE) ||
1150 // |hs->server_params| contains a prefix for signing.
1151 hs->server_params.size() < 2 * SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE ||
1152 !CBB_add_bytes(&body, hs->server_params.data() + 2 * SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE,
1153 hs->server_params.size() - 2 * SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE)) {
1154 return ssl_hs_error;
1155 }
1156
1157 // Add a signature.
1158 if (ssl_cipher_uses_certificate_auth(hs->new_cipher)) {
1159 if (!ssl_has_private_key(hs)) {
1160 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1161 return ssl_hs_error;
1162 }
1163
1164 // Determine the signature algorithm.
1165 uint16_t signature_algorithm;
1166 if (!tls1_choose_signature_algorithm(hs, &signature_algorithm)) {
1167 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
1168 return ssl_hs_error;
1169 }
1170 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_2_VERSION) {
1171 if (!CBB_add_u16(&body, signature_algorithm)) {
1172 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1173 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1174 return ssl_hs_error;
1175 }
1176 }
1177
1178 // Add space for the signature.
1179 const size_t max_sig_len = EVP_PKEY_size(hs->local_pubkey.get());
1180 uint8_t *ptr;
1181 if (!CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &child) ||
1182 !CBB_reserve(&child, &ptr, max_sig_len)) {
1183 return ssl_hs_error;
1184 }
1185
1186 size_t sig_len;
1187 switch (ssl_private_key_sign(hs, ptr, &sig_len, max_sig_len,
1188 signature_algorithm, hs->server_params)) {
1189 case ssl_private_key_success:
1190 if (!CBB_did_write(&child, sig_len)) {
1191 return ssl_hs_error;
1192 }
1193 break;
1194 case ssl_private_key_failure:
1195 return ssl_hs_error;
1196 case ssl_private_key_retry:
1197 return ssl_hs_private_key_operation;
1198 }
1199 }
1200
1201 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
1202 if (!ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
1203 return ssl_hs_error;
1204 }
1205
1206 hs->server_params.Reset();
1207
1208 hs->state = state12_send_server_hello_done;
1209 return ssl_hs_ok;
1210}

1212static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_hello_done(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1213 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1214
1215 ScopedCBB cbb;
1216 CBB body;
1217
1218 if (hs->cert_request) {
1219 CBB cert_types, sigalgs_cbb;
1220 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
1221 SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_REQUEST) ||
1222 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &cert_types) ||
1223 !CBB_add_u8(&cert_types, SSL3_CT_RSA_SIGN) ||
1224 !CBB_add_u8(&cert_types, TLS_CT_ECDSA_SIGN) ||
1225 (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_2_VERSION &&
1226 (!CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &sigalgs_cbb) ||
1227 !tls12_add_verify_sigalgs(hs, &sigalgs_cbb))) ||
1228 !ssl_add_client_CA_list(hs, &body) ||
1229 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
1230 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1231 return ssl_hs_error;
1232 }
1233 }
1234
1235 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
1236 SSL3_MT_SERVER_HELLO_DONE) ||
1237 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
1238 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1239 return ssl_hs_error;
1240 }
1241
1242 hs->state = state12_read_client_certificate;
1243 return ssl_hs_flush;
1244}

1246static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1247 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1248
1249 if (hs->handback && hs->new_cipher->algorithm_mkey == SSL_kECDHE) {
1250 return ssl_hs_handback;
1251 }
1252 if (!hs->cert_request) {
1253 hs->state = state12_verify_client_certificate;
1254 return ssl_hs_ok;
1255 }
1256
1257 SSLMessage msg;
1258 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1259 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1260 }
1261
1262 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE)) {
1263 return ssl_hs_error;
1264 }
1265
1266 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1267 return ssl_hs_error;
1268 }
1269
1270 CBS certificate_msg = msg.body;
1271 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1272 if (!ssl_parse_cert_chain(&alert, &hs->new_session->certs, &hs->peer_pubkey,
1273 hs->config->retain_only_sha256_of_client_certs
1274 ? hs->new_session->peer_sha256
1275 : nullptr,
1276 &certificate_msg, ssl->ctx->pool)) {
1277 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
1278 return ssl_hs_error;
1279 }
1280
1281 if (CBS_len(&certificate_msg) != 0 ||
1282 !ssl->ctx->x509_method->session_cache_objects(hs->new_session.get())) {
1283 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1284 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1285 return ssl_hs_error;
1286 }
1287
1288 if (sk_CRYPTO_BUFFER_num(hs->new_session->certs.get()) == 0) {
1289 // No client certificate so the handshake buffer may be discarded.
1290 hs->transcript.FreeBuffer();
1291
1292 if (hs->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT) {
1293 // Fail for TLS only if we required a certificate
1294 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PEER_DID_NOT_RETURN_A_CERTIFICATE);
1295 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
1296 return ssl_hs_error;
1297 }
1298
1299 // OpenSSL returns X509_V_OK when no certificates are received. This is
1300 // classed by them as a bug, but it's assumed by at least NGINX.
1301 hs->new_session->verify_result = X509_V_OK;
1302 } else if (hs->config->retain_only_sha256_of_client_certs) {
1303 // The hash will have been filled in.
1304 hs->new_session->peer_sha256_valid = 1;
1305 }
1306
1307 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1308 hs->state = state12_verify_client_certificate;
1309 return ssl_hs_ok;
1310}

1312static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_verify_client_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1313 if (sk_CRYPTO_BUFFER_num(hs->new_session->certs.get()) > 0) {
1314 switch (ssl_verify_peer_cert(hs)) {
1315 case ssl_verify_ok:
1316 break;
1317 case ssl_verify_invalid:
1318 return ssl_hs_error;
1319 case ssl_verify_retry:
1320 return ssl_hs_certificate_verify;
1321 }
1322 }
1323
1324 hs->state = state12_read_client_key_exchange;
1325 return ssl_hs_ok;
1326}
1327
1328static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_key_exchange(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1329 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1330 SSLMessage msg;
1331 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1332 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1333 }
1334
1335 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CLIENT_KEY_EXCHANGE)) {
1336 return ssl_hs_error;
1337 }
1338
1339 CBS client_key_exchange = msg.body;
1340 uint32_t alg_k = hs->new_cipher->algorithm_mkey;
1341 uint32_t alg_a = hs->new_cipher->algorithm_auth;
1342
1343 // If using a PSK key exchange, parse the PSK identity.
1344 if (alg_a & SSL_aPSK) {
1345 CBS psk_identity;
1346
1347 // If using PSK, the ClientKeyExchange contains a psk_identity. If PSK,
1348 // then this is the only field in the message.
1349 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&client_key_exchange, &psk_identity) ||
1350 ((alg_k & SSL_kPSK) && CBS_len(&client_key_exchange) != 0)) {
1351 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1352 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1353 return ssl_hs_error;
1354 }
1355
1356 if (CBS_len(&psk_identity) > PSK_MAX_IDENTITY_LEN ||
1357 CBS_contains_zero_byte(&psk_identity)) {
1358 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DATA_LENGTH_TOO_LONG);
1359 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
1360 return ssl_hs_error;
1361 }
1362 char *raw = nullptr;
1363 if (!CBS_strdup(&psk_identity, &raw)) {
1364 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
1365 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1366 return ssl_hs_error;
1367 }
1368 hs->new_session->psk_identity.reset(raw);
1369 }
1370
1371 // Depending on the key exchange method, compute |premaster_secret|.
1372 Array<uint8_t> premaster_secret;
1373 if (alg_k & SSL_kRSA) {
1374 CBS encrypted_premaster_secret;
1375 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&client_key_exchange,
1376 &encrypted_premaster_secret) ||
1377 CBS_len(&client_key_exchange) != 0) {
1378 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1379 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1380 return ssl_hs_error;
1381 }
1382
1383 // Allocate a buffer large enough for an RSA decryption.
1384 Array<uint8_t> decrypt_buf;
1385 if (!decrypt_buf.Init(EVP_PKEY_size(hs->local_pubkey.get()))) {
1386 return ssl_hs_error;
1387 }
1388
1389 // Decrypt with no padding. PKCS#1 padding will be removed as part of the
1390 // timing-sensitive code below.
1391 size_t decrypt_len;
1392 switch (ssl_private_key_decrypt(hs, decrypt_buf.data(), &decrypt_len,
1393 decrypt_buf.size(),
1394 encrypted_premaster_secret)) {
1395 case ssl_private_key_success:
1396 break;
1397 case ssl_private_key_failure:
1398 return ssl_hs_error;
1399 case ssl_private_key_retry:
1400 return ssl_hs_private_key_operation;
1401 }
1402
1403 if (decrypt_len != decrypt_buf.size()) {
1404 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECRYPTION_FAILED);
1405 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR);
1406 return ssl_hs_error;
1407 }
1408
1409 CONSTTIME_SECRET(decrypt_buf.data(), decrypt_len);
1410
1411 // Prepare a random premaster, to be used on invalid padding. See RFC 5246,
1412 // section 7.4.7.1.
1413 if (!premaster_secret.Init(SSL_MAX_MASTER_KEY_LENGTH) ||
1414 !RAND_bytes(premaster_secret.data(), premaster_secret.size())) {
1415 return ssl_hs_error;
1416 }
1417
1418 // The smallest padded premaster is 11 bytes of overhead. Small keys are
1419 // publicly invalid.
1420 if (decrypt_len < 11 + premaster_secret.size()) {
1421 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECRYPTION_FAILED);
1422 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR);
1423 return ssl_hs_error;
1424 }
1425
1426 // Check the padding. See RFC 3447, section 7.2.2.
1427 size_t padding_len = decrypt_len - premaster_secret.size();
1428 uint8_t good = constant_time_eq_int_8(decrypt_buf[0], 0) &
1429 constant_time_eq_int_8(decrypt_buf[1], 2);
1430 for (size_t i = 2; i < padding_len - 1; i++) {
1431 good &= ~constant_time_is_zero_8(decrypt_buf[i]);
1432 }
1433 good &= constant_time_is_zero_8(decrypt_buf[padding_len - 1]);
1434
1435 // The premaster secret must begin with |client_version|. This too must be
1436 // checked in constant time (http://eprint.iacr.org/2003/052/).
1437 good &= constant_time_eq_8(decrypt_buf[padding_len],
1438 (unsigned)(hs->client_version >> 8));
1439 good &= constant_time_eq_8(decrypt_buf[padding_len + 1],
1440 (unsigned)(hs->client_version & 0xff));
1441
1442 // Select, in constant time, either the decrypted premaster or the random
1443 // premaster based on |good|.
1444 for (size_t i = 0; i < premaster_secret.size(); i++) {
1445 premaster_secret[i] = constant_time_select_8(
1446 good, decrypt_buf[padding_len + i], premaster_secret[i]);
1447 }
1448 } else if (alg_k & SSL_kECDHE) {
1449 // Parse the ClientKeyExchange.
1450 CBS peer_key;
1451 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&client_key_exchange, &peer_key) ||
1452 CBS_len(&client_key_exchange) != 0) {
1453 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1454 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1455 return ssl_hs_error;
1456 }
1457
1458 // Compute the premaster.
1459 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1460 if (!hs->key_shares[0]->Finish(&premaster_secret, &alert, peer_key)) {
1461 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
1462 return ssl_hs_error;
1463 }
1464
1465 // The key exchange state may now be discarded.
1466 hs->key_shares[0].reset();
1467 hs->key_shares[1].reset();
1468 } else if (!(alg_k & SSL_kPSK)) {
1469 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1470 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
1471 return ssl_hs_error;
1472 }
1473
1474 // For a PSK cipher suite, the actual pre-master secret is combined with the
1475 // pre-shared key.
1476 if (alg_a & SSL_aPSK) {
1477 if (hs->config->psk_server_callback == NULL) {
1478 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1479 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1480 return ssl_hs_error;
1481 }
1482
1483 // Look up the key for the identity.
1484 uint8_t psk[PSK_MAX_PSK_LEN];
1485 unsigned psk_len = hs->config->psk_server_callback(
1486 ssl, hs->new_session->psk_identity.get(), psk, sizeof(psk));
1487 if (psk_len > PSK_MAX_PSK_LEN) {
1488 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1489 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1490 return ssl_hs_error;
1491 } else if (psk_len == 0) {
1492 // PSK related to the given identity not found.
1493 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PSK_IDENTITY_NOT_FOUND);
1494 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNKNOWN_PSK_IDENTITY);
1495 return ssl_hs_error;
1496 }
1497
1498 if (alg_k & SSL_kPSK) {
1499 // In plain PSK, other_secret is a block of 0s with the same length as the
1500 // pre-shared key.
1501 if (!premaster_secret.Init(psk_len)) {
1502 return ssl_hs_error;
1503 }
1504 OPENSSL_memset(premaster_secret.data(), 0, premaster_secret.size());
1505 }
1506
1507 ScopedCBB new_premaster;
1508 CBB child;
1509 if (!CBB_init(new_premaster.get(),
1510 2 + psk_len + 2 + premaster_secret.size()) ||
1511 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(new_premaster.get(), &child) ||
1512 !CBB_add_bytes(&child, premaster_secret.data(),
1513 premaster_secret.size()) ||
1514 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(new_premaster.get(), &child) ||
1515 !CBB_add_bytes(&child, psk, psk_len) ||
1516 !CBBFinishArray(new_premaster.get(), &premaster_secret)) {
1517 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
1518 return ssl_hs_error;
1519 }
1520 }
1521
1522 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1523 return ssl_hs_error;
1524 }
1525
1526 // Compute the master secret.
1527 hs->new_session->secret_length = tls1_generate_master_secret(
1528 hs, hs->new_session->secret, premaster_secret);
1529 if (hs->new_session->secret_length == 0) {
1530 return ssl_hs_error;
1531 }
1532 hs->new_session->extended_master_secret = hs->extended_master_secret;
1533 CONSTTIME_DECLASSIFY(hs->new_session->secret, hs->new_session->secret_length);
1534 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
1535
1536 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1537 hs->state = state12_read_client_certificate_verify;
1538 return ssl_hs_ok;
1539}
1540
1541static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_certificate_verify(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1542 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1543
1544 // Only RSA and ECDSA client certificates are supported, so a
1545 // CertificateVerify is required if and only if there's a client certificate.
1546 if (!hs->peer_pubkey) {
1547 hs->transcript.FreeBuffer();
1548 hs->state = state12_read_change_cipher_spec;
1549 return ssl_hs_ok;
1550 }
1551
1552 SSLMessage msg;
1553 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1554 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1555 }
1556
1557 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_VERIFY)) {
1558 return ssl_hs_error;
1559 }
1560
1561 // The peer certificate must be valid for signing.
1562 const CRYPTO_BUFFER *leaf =
1563 sk_CRYPTO_BUFFER_value(hs->new_session->certs.get(), 0);
1564 CBS leaf_cbs;
1565 CRYPTO_BUFFER_init_CBS(leaf, &leaf_cbs);
1566 if (!ssl_cert_check_key_usage(&leaf_cbs, key_usage_digital_signature)) {
1567 return ssl_hs_error;
1568 }
1569
1570 CBS certificate_verify = msg.body, signature;
1571
1572 // Determine the signature algorithm.
1573 uint16_t signature_algorithm = 0;
1574 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_2_VERSION) {
1575 if (!CBS_get_u16(&certificate_verify, &signature_algorithm)) {
1576 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1577 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1578 return ssl_hs_error;
1579 }
1580 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1581 if (!tls12_check_peer_sigalg(hs, &alert, signature_algorithm)) {
1582 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
1583 return ssl_hs_error;
1584 }
1585 hs->new_session->peer_signature_algorithm = signature_algorithm;
1586 } else if (!tls1_get_legacy_signature_algorithm(&signature_algorithm,
1587 hs->peer_pubkey.get())) {
1588 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PEER_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_CERTIFICATE_TYPE);
1589 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_CERTIFICATE);
1590 return ssl_hs_error;
1591 }
1592
1593 // Parse and verify the signature.
1594 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&certificate_verify, &signature) ||
1595 CBS_len(&certificate_verify) != 0) {
1596 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1597 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1598 return ssl_hs_error;
1599 }
1600
1601 if (!ssl_public_key_verify(ssl, signature, signature_algorithm,
1602 hs->peer_pubkey.get(), hs->transcript.buffer())) {
1603 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_SIGNATURE);
1604 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR);
1605 return ssl_hs_error;
1606 }
1607
1608 // The handshake buffer is no longer necessary, and we may hash the current
1609 // message.
1610 hs->transcript.FreeBuffer();
1611 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1612 return ssl_hs_error;
1613 }
1614
1615 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1616 hs->state = state12_read_change_cipher_spec;
1617 return ssl_hs_ok;
1618}

1620static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_change_cipher_spec(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1621 if (hs->handback && hs->ssl->session != NULL) {
1622 return ssl_hs_handback;
1623 }
1624 hs->state = state12_process_change_cipher_spec;
1625 return ssl_hs_read_change_cipher_spec;

1628static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_process_change_cipher_spec(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1629 if (!tls1_change_cipher_state(hs, evp_aead_open)) {
1630 return ssl_hs_error;
1631 }
1632
1633 hs->state = state12_read_next_proto;
1634 return ssl_hs_ok;
1635}

1637static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_next_proto(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1638 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1639
1640 if (!hs->next_proto_neg_seen) {
1641 hs->state = state12_read_channel_id;
1642 return ssl_hs_ok;
1643 }
1644
1645 SSLMessage msg;
1646 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1647 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1648 }
1649
1650 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_NEXT_PROTO) ||
1651 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1652 return ssl_hs_error;
1653 }
1654
1655 CBS next_protocol = msg.body, selected_protocol, padding;
1656 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&next_protocol, &selected_protocol) ||
1657 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&next_protocol, &padding) ||
1658 CBS_len(&next_protocol) != 0) {
1659 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1660 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1661 return ssl_hs_error;
1662 }
1663
1664 if (!ssl->s3->next_proto_negotiated.CopyFrom(selected_protocol)) {
1665 return ssl_hs_error;
1666 }
1667
1668 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1669 hs->state = state12_read_channel_id;
1670 return ssl_hs_ok;
1671}

1673static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_channel_id(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1674 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1675
1676 if (!ssl->s3->channel_id_valid) {
1677 hs->state = state12_read_client_finished;
1678 return ssl_hs_ok;
1679 }
1680
1681 SSLMessage msg;
1682 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1683 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1684 }
1685
1686 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CHANNEL_ID) ||
1687 !tls1_verify_channel_id(hs, msg) ||
1688 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1689 return ssl_hs_error;
1690 }
1691
1692 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1693 hs->state = state12_read_client_finished;
1694 return ssl_hs_ok;
1695}

1697static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_finished(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1698 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1699 enum ssl_hs_wait_t wait = ssl_get_finished(hs);
1700 if (wait != ssl_hs_ok) {
1701 return wait;
1702 }
1703
1704 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
1705 hs->state = state12_finish_server_handshake;
1706 } else {
1707 hs->state = state12_send_server_finished;
1708 }
1709
1710 // If this is a full handshake with ChannelID then record the handshake
1711 // hashes in |hs->new_session| in case we need them to verify a
1712 // ChannelID signature on a resumption of this session in the future.
1713 if (ssl->session == NULL && ssl->s3->channel_id_valid &&
1714 !tls1_record_handshake_hashes_for_channel_id(hs)) {
1715 return ssl_hs_error;
1716 }
1717
1718 return ssl_hs_ok;
1719}
1720
1721static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_finished(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1722 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1723
1724 if (hs->ticket_expected) {
1725 const SSL_SESSION *session;
1726 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session_copy;
1727 if (ssl->session == NULL) {
1728 // Fix the timeout to measure from the ticket issuance time.
1729 ssl_session_rebase_time(ssl, hs->new_session.get());
1730 session = hs->new_session.get();
1731 } else {
1732 // We are renewing an existing session. Duplicate the session to adjust
1733 // the timeout.
1734 session_copy =
1735 SSL_SESSION_dup(ssl->session.get(), SSL_SESSION_INCLUDE_NONAUTH);
1736 if (!session_copy) {
1737 return ssl_hs_error;
1738 }
1739
1740 ssl_session_rebase_time(ssl, session_copy.get());
1741 session = session_copy.get();
1742 }
1743
1744 ScopedCBB cbb;
1745 CBB body, ticket;
1746 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
1747 SSL3_MT_NEW_SESSION_TICKET) ||
1748 !CBB_add_u32(&body, session->timeout) ||
1749 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &ticket) ||
1750 !ssl_encrypt_ticket(hs, &ticket, session) ||
1751 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
1752 return ssl_hs_error;
1753 }
1754 }
1755
1756 if (!ssl->method->add_change_cipher_spec(ssl) ||
1757 !tls1_change_cipher_state(hs, evp_aead_seal) ||
1758 !ssl_send_finished(hs)) {
1759 return ssl_hs_error;
1760 }
1761
1762 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
1763 hs->state = state12_read_change_cipher_spec;
1764 } else {
1765 hs->state = state12_finish_server_handshake;
1766 }
1767 return ssl_hs_flush;
1768}
1769
1770static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_finish_server_handshake(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1771 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1772
1773 if (hs->handback) {
1774 return ssl_hs_handback;
1775 }
1776
1777 ssl->method->on_handshake_complete(ssl);
1778
1779 // If we aren't retaining peer certificates then we can discard it now.
1780 if (hs->new_session != NULL &&
1781 hs->config->retain_only_sha256_of_client_certs) {
1782 hs->new_session->certs.reset();
1783 ssl->ctx->x509_method->session_clear(hs->new_session.get());
1784 }
1785
1786 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
1787 ssl->s3->established_session = UpRef(ssl->session);
1788 } else {
1789 ssl->s3->established_session = std::move(hs->new_session);
1790 ssl->s3->established_session->not_resumable = false;
1791 }
1792
1793 hs->handshake_finalized = true;
1794 ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete = true;
1795 ssl_update_cache(hs, SSL_SESS_CACHE_SERVER);
1796
1797 hs->state = state12_done;
1798 return ssl_hs_ok;
1799}

1801enum ssl_hs_wait_t ssl_server_handshake(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1802 while (hs->state != state12_done) {
1803 enum ssl_hs_wait_t ret = ssl_hs_error;
1804 enum tls12_server_hs_state_t state =
1805 static_cast<enum tls12_server_hs_state_t>(hs->state);
1806 switch (state) {
1807 case state12_start_accept:
1808 ret = do_start_accept(hs);
1809 break;
1810 case state12_read_client_hello:
1811 ret = do_read_client_hello(hs);
1812 break;
1813 case state12_read_client_hello_after_ech:
1814 ret = do_read_client_hello_after_ech(hs);
1815 break;
1816 case state12_select_certificate:
1817 ret = do_select_certificate(hs);
1818 break;
1819 case state12_tls13:
1820 ret = do_tls13(hs);
1821 break;
1822 case state12_select_parameters:
1823 ret = do_select_parameters(hs);
1824 break;
1825 case state12_send_server_hello:
1826 ret = do_send_server_hello(hs);
1827 break;
1828 case state12_send_server_certificate:
1829 ret = do_send_server_certificate(hs);
1830 break;
1831 case state12_send_server_key_exchange:
1832 ret = do_send_server_key_exchange(hs);
1833 break;
1834 case state12_send_server_hello_done:
1835 ret = do_send_server_hello_done(hs);
1836 break;
1837 case state12_read_client_certificate:
1838 ret = do_read_client_certificate(hs);
1839 break;
1840 case state12_verify_client_certificate:
1841 ret = do_verify_client_certificate(hs);
1842 break;
1843 case state12_read_client_key_exchange:
1844 ret = do_read_client_key_exchange(hs);
1845 break;
1846 case state12_read_client_certificate_verify:
1847 ret = do_read_client_certificate_verify(hs);
1848 break;
1849 case state12_read_change_cipher_spec:
1850 ret = do_read_change_cipher_spec(hs);
1851 break;
1852 case state12_process_change_cipher_spec:
1853 ret = do_process_change_cipher_spec(hs);
1854 break;
1855 case state12_read_next_proto:
1856 ret = do_read_next_proto(hs);
1857 break;
1858 case state12_read_channel_id:
1859 ret = do_read_channel_id(hs);
1860 break;
1861 case state12_read_client_finished:
1862 ret = do_read_client_finished(hs);
1863 break;
1864 case state12_send_server_finished:
1865 ret = do_send_server_finished(hs);
1866 break;
1867 case state12_finish_server_handshake:
1868 ret = do_finish_server_handshake(hs);
1869 break;
1870 case state12_done:
1871 ret = ssl_hs_ok;
1872 break;
1873 }
1874
1875 if (hs->state != state) {
1876 ssl_do_info_callback(hs->ssl, SSL_CB_ACCEPT_LOOP, 1);
1877 }
1878
1879 if (ret != ssl_hs_ok) {
1880 return ret;
1881 }
1882 }
1883
1884 ssl_do_info_callback(hs->ssl, SSL_CB_HANDSHAKE_DONE, 1);
1885 return ssl_hs_ok;
1886}
